# MOTION SYSTEM

Full motion reference: `docs/reference/design/motion-and-interaction-system.md`

## Stage Engineering Motion Constants

Use these — not the legacy `UNUSONIC_PHYSICS` / `FLUID_SPRING` (or other ad-hoc spring configs):

```typescript
// src/shared/lib/motion-constants.ts
STAGE_HEAVY   // Panels, sheets, full-page elements (stiffness: 180, damping: 28, mass: 1.2)
STAGE_MEDIUM  // Cards, list items, mid-weight elements (stiffness: 300, damping: 26, mass: 0.8)
STAGE_LIGHT   // Chips, badges, toggles, small UI (stiffness: 400, damping: 22, mass: 0.5)
STAGE_NAV_CROSSFADE  // 120ms opacity for route transitions
STAGE_STAGGER_CHILDREN  // 40ms stagger for list items
```

## Rules

1. **No scale on hover.** Hover = light-catch (+0.04 L brightness shift). No `whileHover={{ scale }}`.
2. **No bounce.** All springs are critically damped.
3. **Weight matches mass.** Heavy elements use heavy springs. Light elements use light springs.
4. **Dense tier = instant.** At `data-density="dense"`, state transitions skip animation.
5. **`prefers-reduced-motion`:** Add `<MotionConfig reducedMotion="user">` in root layout. All Framer Motion auto-respects.

## M3 Transition Patterns (Still Apply)

| Pattern | When | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Container transform | One container morphs into another | List item → detail sheet |
| Shared axis | Same content moves along an axis | Stepper flows, tab panels |
| Fade through | Content changes, no shared element | Mode toggles |
| Fade | Simple visibility | Modals, tooltips |

## Code Review Checklist

- [ ] Using STAGE_HEAVY/MEDIUM/LIGHT (not UNUSONIC_PHYSICS, FLUID_SPRING, or ad-hoc inline springs)?
- [ ] No `hover:scale` or `whileHover={{ scale }}`?
- [ ] No `hover:brightness-110`?
- [ ] GPU_STABILIZE applied to moving containers?
- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion` respected?
- [ ] Animating only transform + opacity (no layout/paint)?
